UML:TaggedValue.value: TGGObjectVariable inherits from SDMLanguage::patterns::ObjectVariable. This type is used in TGG rules to declare matches and subsequent manipulation (only CREATE) of objects (i.e. EClasses). In addition to all attributes from ObjectVariables, this subclass references a Domain to denote if it belongs to the source, target or correspondence in the integration.

UML:TaggedValue.value: This package defines all necessary parts to compile a TGG specification into a Ecore + SDM specification. In addition, static analysis should also be modeled in here.

The references to TGGLinkVariable and TGGObjectVariable should redefine the references between StoryPattern and LinkVariable and StoryPattern and ObjectVariable, respectively.
Rules describe declaratively how the triple graph evolves. Rules inherit from SDMLanguage::patterns::StoryPattern, thus from SDMLanguage::NamedElement in order to be able to assign a name to a rule.
Rules can be parameterized and thus contain a set of EParameters.

UML:TaggedValue.value: TGGLinkVariable inherits from SDMLanguage::patterns::LinkVariable. This type is used in TGG rules to declare matches and subsequent manipulation (only CREATE) of links (i.e. EReferences). In addition to all attributes from LinkVariable, this subclass references a domain to denote if it belongs to the source, target or correspondence in the integration.

The outermost container.
A TGG consists of a number of TGG rules, and contains three domains and (for convenience reasons) two or three metamodels (two in the case of an integration between the same metamodel).

UML:TaggedValue.value:
Domains can be of type "SOURCE", "TARGET" or "CORRESPONDENCE" and reference a Metamodel.
A Domain specifies the role a Metamodel plays in an integration. Please note that different Domains can reference the same Metamodel. A Domain therefore wraps/decorates a Metamodel (currently adds a DomainType as "role" and a name).
This package defines all necessary parts to compile a TGG specification into a Ecore + SDM specification. In addition, static analysis should also be modeled in here.
